parameters.name: EndTime
parameters.description:
The end of the time range to query.

This value is a UNIX timestamp representing the number of milliseconds that have elapsed since the epoch time January 1, 1970, 00:00:00 UTC.

parameters.name: EventId
parameters.description: The ID of the custom event.

parameters.name: GroupId
parameters.description: The ID of the application group.

parameters.name: Name
parameters.description: The name of the custom event.

parameters.name: PageNumber
parameters.description: The number of the page to return.

parameters.name: PageSize
parameters.description: The number of entries to return on each page.

parameters.name: SearchKeywords
parameters.description:
The keywords that are contained in the content of the custom event to query. You can use a logical operator between keywords.

*   If you need to query the custom event whose content contains a and b, set the value to a and b.
*   If you need to query the custom event whose content contains a or b, set the value to a or b.

parameters.name: StartTime
parameters.description:
The beginning of the time range to query.

This value is a UNIX timestamp representing the number of milliseconds that have elapsed since the epoch time January 1, 1970, 00:00:00 UTC.
